tip.text: Had lunch at this stall called rama9 thai cuisine. The pineapple rice is delicious with chicken, sort of lunch deal rm13.50(excluding GST) with their ruby dessert. Nice dessert too not too sweet.

formattedAddress: 1 Utama Shopping Centre (Lot S346-S347), Lebuh Bandar Utama
location.address: 1 Utama Shopping Centre (Lot S346-S347), Lebuh Bandar Utama

tip.text: Had the "siap mepanggang". Portion is huge and delicious!! Loved the pulut hitam drink. Service is quick. Yummy...will come back for more.
Like the fries though other than that the bread with the fried shrimps just so so for me. Hot chocolate should be hotter then it be perfect.
This creamy beef bacon spaghetti is just terrible. The black pepper is mulitple small biji and you can taste it when it explode in your mouth. The cream is just too oily. Terrible just terrible.
Had the pizza and seriously its all soggy at the tip end and you can actually see the oil swimming on the pizza and the plate. Asked the waiter for extra plate no manners no reply.
First time here and had the fish cakes, it's delicious. Other than that i had the dried hor fun with fish balls was just so so for me. The boss is friendly.

venue.name: Kedai Makanan Jin Man (金满满茶餐店/阿牛鱼圆粉)

tip.text: This is the most delicious i had in this restaurant. I even finished the whole bread. Service was fast considering I am the only customer in here. Prices are high, wont be back though.
This is delicious !! Chocolate brownie mashmallow ❤️❤️
Always love vivo pizza, staffs are friendly and their quick service. Better than pizza hut. Will come back to try other flavors. Loved the choco brownie marshmallow, really delicious.
The Bacon & Broccoli Linguine is delicious with mild spicy-ness. We had the salmon pizza as well, though the crust is thin but it was filling. Will definitely come back to try other foods.
Loved the Jalapeno bombers, a blast of hotness in your mouth. Definitely lots more delicious than KFC!! Foods are good; coleslaw, mash potato n their biscuits are delicious. Crowdes and limited seats

formattedAddress: Mid Valley Megamall (Lot LG-012), Lingkaran Syed Putra
location.address: Mid Valley Megamall (Lot LG-012), Lingkaran Syed Putra

tip.text: Had this before but never during breakfast time and its was packed. Loved their porridge can compete with my mom's. Price is reasonable with portion given. Got me sweating eating hotporridge ^^ ..
Had the Tori Yakini Chicken Bento; there were not much flavour in the chicken. Rice was so so not hot, not the usual japanese rice. Both side dishes were only cabbage with some mayo.

formattedAddress: Ground Flr, Sunway Medical Center (Jl. Lagoon Selatan)

tip.text: First time here. Had the fire balls and the pineapple fried rice, good taste with different spices filling up ur palate. Had the peanut and coconut ice cream, its good. Will be back to try others.
My 2nd time here and ordered again the pumpkin soup. Pizza is just okay for me.

formattedAddress: The Gardens Mall (Lot LG-K09, LG Floor)

tip.text: Had the boyfriend steak sandwich, the bread was hard and the meat was rubbery. There were no seasoning in the meat. This is how they pack my leftover in the box-all campak in. Will not come back!!
RM2.00 for the noodle, RM2.50 for the hot milo. Food tastes quite good though the milo slightly over priced compared to outside. Nice environment here in cafe. Hospital parkings r limited tho.
Wished this chocolate drink more hot then it be delicious to enjoy. Parking was quite confusing bit senget here and there. Regardless how long/short time u park, still have to buy parking token RM7.
Had this sizzling beef noodle at the stall called Hot Plate. Loved the beef, not tangy and the hot plate kept the food warm till the last noodle. The owner of stall is from Taiwan & he is friendly 👍
My 2nd time here and i ordered the KGB spiked again. This time it didn't blow my taste buds away like the first time, something is missing here. Will try the double animal next time if i go again.

formattedAddress: The Gardens Mall (Lot LG-232B&C, LG Floor)

tip.text: 15/3 1pm: Waiters more friendly than the botak wearing spectacles man at the cashier. Told him i'm using hong leong debit card;x response, told dont want the wet tissue;x response...lan shi !!
Only me and husband in the restaurant at this hour (130pm), the environment quite nice and the waitress who served us is friendly. The chicken is grilled perfectly, only its a little salty i feel.
Employees all staring the grill place area instead of looking out towards where customers sit. Been here b4 & yes really need to improve staffs attitude. Today they told me chocolate no stock ... 😡😡

Been here since 730pm and sitted back of restaurant in a room, electric was out more than 3 times. Our waitress underaged. Lou sang done and yet our food is not here, waitress say still cooking!! OMFG

formattedAddress: No. 157, Jalan Limau Besar, Kawasan 18 (Jalan Limau Besar)

tip.text: I had their taufufa today first time and its really good. I like the environment here, quiet and comfy. Only one thing turns me off was the music they playing, repeat the same one again & again.
I always had the char keow teow at Lorong Seratus Tahun when i am here. Keow teow is cooked to perfection with 2 medium fresh prawns but u got to eat while its hot. Dry curry mee is delicious too.
The dessert I ordered almond paste tasted like its mixed from powder packet. Wantan mee not bad as the wanton is nice to eat. My mui choy rice I wished it be hotter the rice. Maybe wont come back la.
